 England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Upholland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"nl":{" 1448–1500":"1448–1500","1448–1500":"1448–1500","1442–1558":"1442–1558","1468–1520":"1468–1520","1468–Female":"1468–Overleden","1425–1448":"1425–1448","1428–Female":"1428–Overleden","1448":"1448","1558":"1558","1425":"1425","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","about 1468":"circa 1468","1442":"1442"," 1448":"1448","1428":"1428","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Upholland, Lancashire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"en":{" 1448–1500":"1448–1500","1448–1500":"1448–1500","1442–1558":"1442–1558","1468–1520":"1468–1520","1468–Female":"1468–Deceased","1425–1448":"1425–1448","1428–Female":"1428–Deceased","1448":"1448","1558":"1558","1425":"1425","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","about 1468":"about 1468","1442":"1442"," 1448":"1448","1428":"1428","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Upholland, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"FitzAlan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English: relationship name from Anglo-Norman French  <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ (  see  Fitz  ) + the personal name  <i>Alan</i> (  see  Allen  ), ‘son of  <i>Alan</i>’."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]},{"name":"Allen","meanings":["English and Scottish: from the Middle English, Old French personal name <i>Alain</i>, <i>Alein</i> (Old Breton <i>Alan</i>), from a Celtic personal name of great antiquity and obscurity. In England the personal name is now usually spelled <i>Alan</i>, the surname <i>Allen</i>; in Scotland the surname is more often <i>Allan</i>. From 1139 it was common in Scotland, where the surname also derives from Gaelic <i>Ailéne</i>, <i>Ailín</i>, from <i>ail</i> ‘rock’. The present-day frequency of the surname Allen in England and Ireland is partly accounted for by the popularity of the personal name among Breton followers of William the Conqueror, by whom it was imported first to Britain and then to Ireland. Saint Alan(us) was a 5th-century bishop of Quimper, who was a cult figure in medieval Brittany. Another Saint Al(l)an was a Cornish or Breton saint of the 6th century, to whom a church in Cornwall is dedicated.","English: occasionally perhaps from the rare Middle English femaje personal name <i>Aline</i> (Old French <i>Adaline</i>, <i>Aaline</i>), a pet form of ancient Germanic names in <i>Adal-</i>, especially <i>Adalheidis</i> (see   Allis  ).","French: variant of   Allain  , a cognate of 1 above, and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice FitzAlan was born in 1448, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, Richard FitzAlan, was 23 and her mother, Alice De Warenne, was 20. She married Sir Roger De Holland in 1468, in Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1500, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 52."},"et":{" 1448–1500":"1448–1500","1448–1500":"1448–1500","1442–1558":"1442–1558","1468–1520":"1468–1520","1468–Female":"1468–Surnud","1425–1448":"1425–1448","1428–Female":"1428–Surnud","1448":"1448","1558":"1558","1425":"1425","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","about 1468":"umbes 1468","1442":"1442"," 1448":"1448","1428":"1428","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Upholland, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{" 1448–1500":"1448–1500","1448–1500":"1448–1500","1442–1558":"1442–1558","1468–1520":"1468–1520","1468–Female":"1468–Kuollut","1425–1448":"1425–1448","1428–Female":"1428–Kuollut","1448":"1448","1558":"1558","1425":"1425","1468":"1468","1500":"1500","1520":"1520","about 1468":"noin 1468","1442":"1442"," 1448":"1448","1428":"1428","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Upholland, Lancashire, England":"Upholland, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti